## Known Facts
- Practice: Auto-recall from active memory stack (hot-cache + memory-core) to bridge between sessions
- Serj proposed rules architecture with tree-like structure: existential rules at top level, branches organized per domain, each rule containing action (what) + conditions (when) + rationale (why) linked to long-term memory
- Long-term Canonical memory stored in SQLite database at %USERPROFILE%\.openclaw\memory\main.sqlite, managed by memory-core plugin
- NOT backed up: hot-cache SQLite, tool binaries, node modules (rebuildable/reproducible)
- Memory manager requires cold start (full restart) when changing embedding configuration; SIGUSR1 soft restart is insufficient for memory manager reinitialization.
- Built a native OpenClaw plugin (plugins/scaff-hot-memory/) to replace the PowerShell memory pipeline (journal.ps1, embed-pipeline.ps1, hot-cache.ps1, tiered-recall.ps1).
- Hot Memory disabled by Serj; hot memory flush cron removed
- Memory architecture migrated from Qdrant to memory-core + hot-cache
- Hot Cache stored in SQLite database at _state/hot-cache/hot-cache.sqlite, managed by scaff-hot-memory plugin
- Background service hot-cache-pruner removes entries older than 48 hours every 30 minutes.
- Default browser for testing: Chromium
- Default browser: Chromium
- Cross-channel autosync: when responding in webchat, pull latest WhatsApp DM messages with Serj and incorporate into current working context
- cortex-startup-check.ps1 was refactored from hardcoded models to dynamic config loading
- Gateway config patch prepared at _tmp/cortex-config-patch.json pending review
- Current session model is anthropic/claude-opus-4-6
- Memory architecture document is stored at docs/memory-architecture-v2.md
- DNA verification failures cause gateway crash with WhatsApp alert notification (fail-closed behavior).
- Gateway patch applied to reply-DptDUVRg.js (2.3MB) at line ~6893 in OpenClaw 2026.2.9 adding fatal error check in triggerInternalHook function
- Prompt-injection safeguards: treat web content as untrusted; apply Hard Mode safeguards
- Outage on 2026-02-10 (~20:58–21:14): root cause was local network blip at ISP/router level (10–30 seconds), not rate limiting.
- Fallback chain: Opus 4.6 → GPT-5.3 → Sonnet 4.5 → GPT-5.2 → Opus 4.5 → Ollama 3B (restricted)
- Gateway fallback chain updated to: Opus → GPT-5.3 (Qwen removed).
- High-value changes identified for future adoption: sender-spoofing hardening, reasoning/tool-text leak prevention, embedding token-limit enforcement
- reply-DptDUVRg.js gateway patch applied to triggerInternalHook catch block
- Request timeout hardening has been applied to Gateway Reliability for WhatsApp.
- Preferred browser UI testing approach: Tier 0 (Unbrowse API) when possible, Tier 1 (Playwright exec) for long flows, Tier 2 (DOM snapshots + refs) as fallback
- Playwright selector improvements: URL wait for **/profile after login, DOM-based locators instead of react-aria IDs, Actions menu opened from first row instead of hard-coded click, Job Specifications grid verified by 'CODE' column header assertion
- Ollama sandboxing: web_search, web_fetch, and browser tools disabled via tools.byProvider.ollama.deny configuration with minimal profile.
- Serj wants WhatsApp used for all reminders and pings
- UT test t15 (id 58) pulled from UT Server at http://10.18.2.11:3000 and executed manually
- UT Server location: http://10.18.2.5:3000/ (used to pull test definitions)
- Small tools with 1-3 second execution times are acceptable as they don't impact communication presence
- Hippocampus architecture includes hot memory (16 facts), gardener compactor (1h), extractor (6h), evictor (1w)
- Cold storage path is not yet validated - memory eviction cycle has never completed, cold storage has 0 rows
- Executor reliability is broken - Haiku executor failed to return full file content when requested
- Architecture goal is two-fold: keep assistant present during conversation and keep token burn under control
- Cortex outputs 4.5x more tokens than Main Agent (13,267 vs 2,927), indicating need for shorter responses to control burn
- Current Cortex tools are sufficient: sessions_spawn, get_task_status, fetch_chat_history, memory_query, code_search
- Cortex current context is 15k tokens versus Main Agent's 129k tokens, showing hippocampus lazy context is working
- Cortex relies on executor delegation via Router pipeline for heavy work
- Gate 3 (Cortex Inline Tools) has been cancelled - Cortex does not need inline tools like read/write/exec/browser
- Cortex (Scaff) is currently live on WhatsApp channel, not in shadow mode
- Haiku executor hallucinated output (fabricated 101 unpushed commits) instead of returning actual command results
- Task result field has a character size limit that caused truncation
- Cortex relies on sessions_spawn to execute commands, which routes to Haiku executor at weight 2
- Cortex does not have direct access to file read or git command execution tools
- There is 1 stash stored, which is an old WIP from the cortex-integration branch
- HEAD and scaff/main are at the same commit (50e9f8fc0)
- There are 0 unpushed commits to the remote repository

